Results.ReviewText: Large and wide enough for great coverage with excellent leakage protection. Roomy crotch for additional absorbent pad. Tough outer shell and velcro tabs do not easily tear while pulling them on my elderly mother where front and rear anatomy parts are in the way.
Results.Title: Great Product

Results.ReviewText: I bought these two months ago for my daughter and they work great. She has sensitive skin and thus has been a great product for us
Results.Title: Great product

Results.ReviewText: The briefs I purchased most are comfortable, but most importantly, I am protected each night. I have struggled with other products, but finally I have what I needed. Thank you so much!!!
Results.Title: Perfect Fit!

Results.ReviewText: My husband uses the Air-Supreme briefs at night and Air-Supreme light briefs during the day. The briefs are comfortable and there have been no leaks with this product. I wish we would have found this product sooner. Don't rely on over the counter products, they are not made well. This product is simply amazing and well worth the money. My husband has been using the briefs for over a year now and he is very pleased with them.
Results.Title: Amazing product

Results.ReviewText:
I use these for my 9 year old son. I only use them over night. I don't have to worry about any leaking. He sleeps through the night.
This is even with a feeding pump which is continuous feed during the night.
Results.Title: Absorbent

Results.ReviewText: I have a special needs child that is about to turn 12. He is in diapers and may be forever. Although we still have leakouts on a daily basis I'm not sure what we would do had we not found these diapers. I hope the manufacturer continues to improve the product. Itsna really good one but it would be nice not to have any leaks.
Results.Title: Lifesaver

Results.ReviewText: We use this product for my son who is a very slim 9 year old for night time incontinence. It works well and keeps the bed dry almost every night. I haven't figured out why it is "almost." Not sure if we don't get the 4 straps completely secured or if it a volume issue. I prefer this style with 2 closures on each side versus the product labelled for children that had one closure on each side. Overall quite happy.
Results.Title: works well

Results.ReviewText: Love these briefs only thing I would suggest is to put adhesive tape to the backing to prevent moving
Results.Title: Love these

Results.ReviewText:
I received a sample two pack of these with my order of the regular Supreme Briefs.
These have the same amazing absorbency, with the added benefit of re-attachable tapes (Velcro Like style). The cloth like outside is much more quiet than the plastic backed supreme briefs and is overall a very comfortable diaper.

These things should be called Super Soakers I tell you what!
I have a large bladder that spasms when its full, which empties it all at once.
These diapers have held up to the task. Not a single leak with these or their plastic backed twins. They also work very well for Bowel Incontinence, (I have IBS).

Overall, highly recommended for any incontinence needs!
I will be buying many more over the years.
Results.Title: One of the Best
